               'and direction of the neutrons. Other parameters are common to '
               'all sources, including those related to neutron energies or '
               'how many neutrons to generate.',
 'src_list': [{'name': 'constant',
               'descr': 'A source which always provide the same position and '
                        'direction of the initial neutron.',
               'specific_params': [['x', '0', 'x coordinate of position [m].'],
                                   ['y', '0', 'y coordinate of position [m].'],
                                   ['z', '0', 'z coordinate of position [m].'],
                                   ['ux', '0', 'x coordinate of direction.'],
                                   ['uy', '0', 'y coordinate of direction.'],
                                   ['uz', '1', 'z coordinate of direction.']],
               'sort_key': 0},
              {'name': 'circular',
               'descr': 'A source which allows modelling of a beam of uniform '
                        'circular cross section. Specifically, all neutrons '
                        'are generated with a fixed direction, and with a '
                        'position sampled uniformly within a disk of radius r. '
                        'The center of the disk is configurable, while its '
                        'normal is always parallel to the direction of the '
                        'neutrons.',
               'specific_params': [['x',
                                    '0',
                                    'x coordinate of disk center [m].'],
                                   ['y',
                                    '0',
                                    'y coordinate of disk center [m].'],
                                   ['z',
                                    '0',
                                    'z coordinate of disk center [m].'],
                                   ['ux', '0', 'x coordinate of direction.'],
                                   ['uy', '0', 'y coordinate of direction.'],
                                   ['uz', '1', 'z coordinate of direction.']],
               'sort_key': 1},
              {'name': 'isotropic',
               'descr': 'A source which emits neutrons isotropically from a '
                        'particular point or spherical surface.',
               'specific_params': [['x', '0', 'x coordinate of position [m].'],
                                   ['y', '0', 'y coordinate of position [m].'],
                                   ['z', '0', 'z coordinate of position [m].'],
                                   ['r',
                                    '0',
                                    'Signed radius of sphere. Neutrons are '
                                    'always first placed on the point (x,y,z) '
                                    'and assigned an isotropically sampled '
                                    'direction. If r!=0, the position is then '
                                    'translated a distance of -r along that '
                                    'direction.']],
               'sort_key': 2}],
 'commonpars_descr': 'For all sources, the parameter "n" (default 1e6) is used '
                     'to specify the number of neutrons to generate.',
 'commonpars_energy_descr': 'Parameters "ekin" and "wl" are also common to all '
                            'sources, and allow for a flexible specification '
                            'of the generated neutron energies, as shown by '
                            'these examples:',
 'commonpars_energy_examples': [['ekin=0.025',
                                 'All neutrons are generated with an energy of '
                                 '0.025eV.'],
                                ['ekin=0.025-0.05',
                                 'Neutron energies are sampled uniformly in '
                                 'the interval [0.025eV,0.050eV].'],
                                ['ekin=0.025+-0.001',
                                 'Neutron energies are sampled from a '
                                 'log-normal distribution with mean 0.025eV '
                                 'and RMS 0.001eV.'],
                                ['ekin=thermal:77K',
                                 'Neutron energies are sampled from a thermal '
                                 '(Maxwell) distribution at 77K.'],
                                ['wl=1.8',
                                 'All neutrons are generated with a wavelength '
                                 'of 1.8Aa.'],
                                ['wl=1.8-5',
                                 'Neutron wavelengths are sampled uniformly in '
                                 'the interval [1.8Aa,5Aa].'],
                                ['wl=1.8+-0.01',
                                 'Neutron wavelengths are sampled from a '
                                 'log-normal distribution with mean 1.8Aa and '
                                 'RMS 0.01Aa.']],
 'commonpars_list': ['ekin', 'wl', 'n'],
 'examples': [['constant;wl=1.8;z=-0.1',
